any’. Some of the modern forms are from the Middle English <i>Brytane</i>, <i>Brittan</i> ‘Breton’; compare   Breton  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Muircheartach Ó Briain King of Thomond was born in Ennis, County Clare, Ireland as the son of Toirdhealbhach Mór Ó Briain, King of Thomond and Orflath Mac Carthy Mor. He married Éadaoin Nic Gormáin Queen of Thomond in 1300, in Ennis, County Clare, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He registered for military service in 1317. He died on 5 June 1343, in his hometown, and was buried in Ennis 1, Ennis, County Clare, Ireland."},"et":{"–5 June 1343":"–5. juuni 1343","–1343":"–1343","–1360":"–1360","–Male":"Surnud","1285–1367":"1285–1367","1315–Male":"1315–Surnud","–1380":"–1380","–1398":"–1398","1245–1306":"1245–1306","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","from 1317 to 1343":"1317 kuni 1343","Abt 1315":"umbes 1315","1285":"1285","1360":"1360","5 June 1343":"5. juuni 1343","1270":"1270","1380":"1380","1315":"1315","1367":"1367","1300":"1300","1245":"1245","1398":"1398","1343":"1343","15 August 1317":"15. august 1317","1306":"1306","Ennis, Clare, Munster, Ireland":"Ennis, County Clare, Iirimaa","near Corcomroe Abbey, County Clare, Ireland":"Corcomroe, County Clare, Iirimaa","Ennis Abbey, Ennis, Clare, Ireland":"Ennis 1, Ennis, County Clare, Iirimaa","Second wife of Turlogh Mor":"Of, Trabzon, Türgi","Ennis Friary, Ennis, Clare, Munster, Ireland":"Ennis, County Clare, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"–5 June 1343":"–5. kesäkuuta 1343","–1343":"–1343","–1360":"–1360","–Male":"Kuollut","1285–1367":"1285–1367","1315–Male":"1315–Kuollut","–1380":"–1380","–1398":"–1398","1245–1306":"1245–1306","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","from 1317 to 1343":"vuodesta 1317 vuoteen 1343","Abt 1315":"noin 1315","1285":"1285","1360":"1360","5 June 1343":"5. kesäkuuta 1343","1270":"1270","1380":"1380","1315":"1315","1367":"1367","1300":"1300","1245":"1245","1398":"1398","1343":"1343","15 August 1317":"15. elokuuta 1317","1306":"1306","Ennis, Clare, Munster, Ireland":"Ennis